[Measles is by no means absent from Canada as the archived ProMED-mail
reports below demonstrate. It is indicative of an efficient public
health service that the city of Ottawa has been free of locally
transmitted measles for a period of 15 years up to the present
incident. This new case of locally transmitted measles reveals the
vulnerability of any population where vaccination is less than
universal.

A map of Ontario showing the location of Ottawa can be accessed at:
<http://www.canada-maps.org/ontario-map.htm>. The
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Canada is available at:
<http://healthmap.org/r/007x>. - Mod.CP]
